p On a good day, you fall asleep easily: willing and able to end the day. When you have insomnia, however, you find it difficult to fall asleep without sedatives. Even people who are not bipolar may have difficulty ending the day without alcohol.
p The BipolarType theory asserts that although you can have more or less insomnia on different days (Bipolar) the form of your insomnia remains the same (Type).
